steps.description:
Create a custom IDP that uses the `ConfiguredProvider` interface:

1. Implement `IdentityProviderFactory` (for user-defined IDPs) or `SocialIdentityProviderFactory` (for social IDPs)
2. Implement the `ConfiguredProvider` interface to expose configuration properties:
```java
@Override
public List<ProviderConfigProperty> getConfigProperties() {
    List<ProviderConfigProperty> props = new ArrayList<>();
    ProviderConfigProperty prop = new ProviderConfigProperty();
    prop.setName("customField");
    prop.setLabel("Custom Field");
    prop.setType(ProviderConfigProperty.STRING_TYPE);
    prop.setHelpText("A custom configuration field");
    props.add(prop);
    return props;
}
```
3. Package the provider as a JAR and deploy it to `/opt/keycloak/providers/`
4. Rebuild Keycloak: `/opt/keycloak/bin/kc.sh build`

See the [source issue](https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/issues/15344) for community discussion and examples.
